---
import StarlightPage from '@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro';
---

<StarlightPage
  frontmatter={{
    title: 'API Explorer',
    description: 'Interactive reference for the mxr HTTP bridge. Try requests against your local daemon at http://127.0.0.1:7777.',
    template: 'splash',
    pagefind: false,
  }}
>
  <p>
    The mxr daemon serves an OpenAPI 3.1 spec at <code>/api/v1/openapi.json</code> when
    <code>[bridge]&nbsp;enabled&nbsp;=&nbsp;true</code> in your config (default). The explorer below
    is rendered from the spec generated during this site's build.
  </p>

  <p>
    To try requests, start the daemon (<code>mxr</code> or <code>mxr daemon</code>), grab your
    bearer token from <code>~/.config/mxr/bridge-token</code>, and click <strong>Authorize</strong>
    in the explorer.
  </p>

  <p>
    If the embedded explorer does not load, open the raw spec at
    <a href="/openapi.json"><code>/openapi.json</code></a>.
  </p>

  <noscript>
    <p>
      The interactive explorer requires JavaScript. The raw spec is at
      <a href="/openapi.json"><code>/openapi.json</code></a>.
    </p>
  </noscript>

  <div id="scalar-api-reference" style="margin-top: 2rem; min-height: 80vh;">
    <p>Loading API Explorer...</p>
  </div>

  <script
    is:inline
    id="api-reference"
    data-url="/openapi.json"
    data-configuration='{"theme":"default","darkMode":true,"hideClientButton":false,"servers":[{"url":"http://127.0.0.1:7777","description":"Local mxr daemon"}]}'
  ></script>
  <script
    is:inline
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@scalar/api-reference@1.55.1"
  ></script>
</StarlightPage>
